        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 5:10PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 509 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Harleton, or 17 miles northwest of Marshall, moving northeast at 40
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Diana, Lassater, Jefferson, Lodi, Fairview, Pruett, Smithland,
Avinger, Linden, Berea, Harleton, Kildare, and Nesbitt.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until midnight CDT for northwestern
Louisiana...and northeastern Texas.</instruction>
